title: Bug 110566 - Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set
description: When setting the filter to 'row[0] equals to 0', the result set is returned incorrectly. It either returns null or an invalid result set.
OB: When setting the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set result is returned incorrectly.
EB: The data set result should be returned correctly when setting the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0'.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Set the filter expression to 'row[0] equals to 0'. 2. Observe that the data set result is returned incorrectly.
